Maintainer: VITOS Team <vitos@vit.example>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: vitos-ghost
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, vitos-base, vitos-monitor,
 wireguard, wireguard-tools, tor, torsocks,
 nftables, iproute2, macchanger, dnscrypt-proxy,
 jq, curl
Description: VITOS Ghost Mode — WireGuard/Tor netns + nftables kill-switch
 Authorized faculty / PhD researchers can opt into a network namespace
 routed entirely through WireGuard or Tor with MAC randomization, hostname
 spoofing, and a hard nftables kill-switch that drops all traffic if the
 tunnel goes down. Activation requires dual-admin approval via
 'vitosctl ghost enable' / 'vitosctl ghost approve' — a member of the
 vitos-admins group requests, a member of vitos-ghost-approvers approves,
 and a single user cannot self-approve. All ghost-mode sessions are still
 logged internally to /var/log/vitos/events.jsonl and alerts.jsonl —
 Ghost Mode hides the *external* trace, not the academic-integrity audit.
